<span class="displaytext">arlington, va -- today, (candidate last)-palin 2008 campaign spokesman ben porritt released the following statement: <p>"given his deep and longstanding ties to acorn, (candidate full) must immediately come clean with the american people about his relationship with the left-wing, activist organization. already under investigation for voter fraud in 14 states, acorn's illegal activities threaten to undermine the integrity of our (PARTY NAME) process. (candidate full)'s association with acorn demonstrates stunningly bad judgment and troubling blind ambition." </p><p><b><u>the facts:</u></b> <b> <ul><li>(candidate full) started working with acorn in 1992</li></ul> <ul><li>(candidate full) was acorn's lawyer</li></ul> <ul><li>(candidate full) trained acorn staff</li></ul> <ul><li>when (candidate full) was on the board of directors of the woods fund, acorn received $190,000 of grants from the organization</li></ul> <ul><li>(candidate full)'s campaign paid over $800,000 to an acorn affiliate for get-out-the-vote efforts</li></ul> <ul><li>acorn's political action committee endorsed (candidate full)</li></ul> (candidate full) started working with acorn in 1992.</b> "what's more, (candidate last) worked as executive director of acorn's voter-registration arm, project vote, in 1992." (editorial, "is acorn stealing the election?" <a href="http://www.ibdeditorials.com/ibdarticles.aspx?id=308358130652174">investor's business daily</a>, 10/8/08) </p><p><b>(candidate full) represented acorn in a lawsuit.</b> "the latest wave of acorn investigations has provided (PARTY NAME)s with both an opening to assail an old foe, and a new line of criticism to use against the (PARTY NAME) presidential nominee, who represented acorn in a lawsuit in the 1990s." (alexander burns, "acorn gives gop new line of attack," <a href="http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1008/14492.html">politico</a>, 10/11/08) </p><p><b>(candidate full) trained acorn staff.</b> "at the time, talbot worked at the social action group acorn and initially considered (candidate last) a competitor. but she became so impressed with his work that she invited him to help train her staff." (letta tayler and keith herbert, "(candidate last) forged path as chicago community organizer," <a href="http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/ny-usobam025598601mar02,1,6933215,full.story">los angeles times</a>, 3/2/08) </p><p><b>when (candidate full) was on the board of directors of the woods fund, acorn received $190,000 of grants from the organization.</b> (donors forum website, <a href="http://ifs.donorsforum.org/">ifs.donorsforum.org</a>, accessed 6/10/08) </p><p><b>(candidate full)'s campaign "paid more than $800,000" to an acorn affiliate for get-out-the vote efforts.</b> "u.s. sen. (candidate full)'s presidential campaign paid more than $800,000 to an offshoot of the liberal association of community organizations for reform now for services the (PARTY NAME)'s campaign says it mistakenly misrepresented in federal reports." (david m. brown, "(candidate last) to amend report on $800,000 in spending," pittsburgh tribune review, 8/22/08) </p><p><b>acorn's political action committee endorsed (candidate full).</b> "acorn's political action committee, acorn votes, announced feb. 21 that it had endorsed sen. (candidate full) for president." (acorn, "acorn's political action committee endorses (candidate last)," press <a href="http://www.acorn.org/index.php?id=8539&amp;l=1%26tx_ttnews[pointer]%3d3%26chash%3d80ab1e121c&amp;tx_ttnews[pointer]=7&amp;tx_ttnews[tt_news]=21759&amp;tx_ttnews[backpid]=8538&amp;chash=43d9ec462f">release</a>, 2/21/08)</p></span>



